                            p.lead.mb-0 Get access to fast connection, public transportation and clean energy while living in natural and rural places
                    .col-lg-4
                        .features-icons-item.mx-auto.mb-0.mb-lg-3
                            .features-icons-icon.d-flex
                                i.bi-person-heart.m-auto.text-primary
                            h3 Know your neighbors
                            p.lead.mb-0 Create your community before moving or enter an existing one looking for you

        // Image Showcases
        section.showcase
            .container-fluid.p-0
                .row.g-0
                    .col-lg-6.order-lg-2.text-white.showcase-img(style="background-image: url('assets/img/sorin-gheorghita-edGsA4qxDaE-unsplash.jpg');")
                    .col-lg-6.order-lg-1.my-auto.showcase-text
                        h2 City life is unhealty and not sustainable
                        p.lead.mb-0
                            | While living in a metropolis has its perks, it can take a big toll on our physical and mental health. Air pollution, high noise levels, crowded public transportation, heavy traffic are just some of the problems. The consequences on our health are more than what you could imagine
                            br
                            br
                            a(target="_blank", href="https://www.healthline.com/health/mental-health/living-in-a-city#Living-in-a-city-can-also-affect-your-sleep-quality-and-cardiovascular-health") Find out more
                .row.g-0
                    .col-lg-6.text-white.showcase-img(style="background-image: url('assets/img/sergiu-valena-MnVFPzf5r2Y-unsplash.jpg');")
                    .col-lg-6.my-auto.showcase-text
                        h2 Italy is giving away ancient villages 
                        p.lead.mb-0
                            | Starting from a small village in Sicily, the initiative to buy "houses for 1 euro" allows you to buy a rather old property to be renovated at the symbolic price of 1 euro: usually these are small municipalities at risk of depopulation located in rural areas.
                            br
                            br
                            a(target="_blank", href="https://www.google.com/maps/d/viewer?mid=1V9V8huzhFYGTQxcRjHjxFNEN5SI-HZ0F&ll=42.54432497101146%2C11.299738438138478&z=4") Check the map
                .row.g-0
                    .col-lg-6.order-lg-2.text-white.showcase-img(style="background-image: url('assets/img/artur-voznenko-ps6D2gxn384-unsplash.jpg');")
                    .col-lg-6.order-lg-1.my-auto.showcase-text
                        h2 What is Alborgo?
                        p.lead.mb-0
                            | Alborgo is a system of eco-villages. We find and renew houses while creating communities that will live there. All the Alborgo users will have the right to live in an Italian village of their choice for medium or long periods, they will be able to move to other Alborgo realities in a blink of an eye without incurring in additional expenses and getting to know your neighbors by subscribing to a monthly or annual subscription.
                            br
                            br
                            a(target="_blank", href="https://b0qwudfistl.typeform.com/to/aN37Y597") Get involved

